00:00:00,010 --> 00:00:01,930
[ Watch on kissasia.li ]

1
00:00:01,106 --> 00:00:03,108
[♪ upbeat music plays]

2
00:00:30,427 --> 00:00:34,056
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

3
00:00:44,149 --> 00:00:46,902
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION
SOME SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

4
00:00:46,985 --> 00:00:49,071
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:00:52,282 --> 00:00:54,701
[Jiui] My punishment was long overdue…

6
00:00:58,372 --> 00:01:00,207
and I think it's finally time.

7
00:01:04,127 --> 00:01:06,505
A friend of mine died because of me.

8
00:01:11,718 --> 00:01:13,053
On an island.

9
00:01:17,307 --> 00:01:19,976
I'm the one who sent Seonu out to sea.

10
00:01:38,495 --> 00:01:41,331
I swore I'd never allow myself
a moment of happiness…

11
00:01:49,047 --> 00:01:51,133
but I guess I got too greedy.

12
00:01:56,346 --> 00:01:57,806
[Jiui sighs]

13
00:02:06,022 --> 00:02:12,988
EPISODE 11
RECONCILIATION, HEALING, AND…

14
00:02:19,161 --> 00:02:23,123
You all saw the news, right?
About how Dr. Do's on medication.

15
00:02:23,206 --> 00:02:26,168
-Shut that mouth of yours.
-It's just, the meds he's on--

16
00:02:26,251 --> 00:02:28,628
Hey, I told you to shut it.

17
00:02:28,712 --> 00:02:30,714
Name one person here who isn't on meds.

18
00:02:30,797 --> 00:02:33,467
So stop yapping and making
such a big deal out of nothing.

19
00:02:33,550 --> 00:02:36,553
Jeez, why do you keep telling me
to shut it?

20
00:02:36,636 --> 00:02:41,224
I was just trying to say
that someone must have ratted out Dr. Do.

21
00:02:41,308 --> 00:02:45,020
It's not like we're gonna
gossip behind his back.

22
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:47,355
We're all family here.

23
00:02:47,439 --> 00:02:48,648
You worry too much.

24
00:02:48,732 --> 00:02:51,193
That's the part that bothers me a little.

25
00:02:51,276 --> 00:02:55,322
-That kind of personal info is top secret.
-Of course.

26
00:02:55,405 --> 00:02:57,657
So who could have snitched
to the county office?

27
00:02:57,741 --> 00:02:58,742
That's true.

28
00:02:58,825 --> 00:03:02,621
Whoever it was must have held
a grudge against Dr. Do, you know?

29
00:03:02,704 --> 00:03:06,041
Oh, my! Chugging soju this early?

30
00:03:06,124 --> 00:03:08,335
Hey, Geumja, give me
a bowl of seafood ramyeon.

31
00:03:08,418 --> 00:03:09,461
Seafood ramyeon? Okay.

32
00:03:10,629 --> 00:03:13,840
So what are we talking about?

33
00:03:14,716 --> 00:03:16,676
Were you talking about that doctor?

34
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:18,512
Damn, that one's a riot.

35
00:03:18,595 --> 00:03:20,514
He's on medication.

36
00:03:20,597 --> 00:03:23,058
So you think someone
being on medication's a riot?

37
00:03:23,141 --> 00:03:26,436
It's a bit late,
but isn't it such a relief

38
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:28,688
that such vital information
has come to light?

39
00:03:30,232 --> 00:03:34,444
So, were you the one who did it?
STYLE
::cue()

40
00:03:35,028 --> 00:03:39,991
Did you ruin his future
because he kept meddling in your affairs?

41
00:03:40,075 --> 00:03:42,994
Have you lost your marbles, old man?

42
00:03:43,078 --> 00:03:44,829
What the hell are you talking about?

43
00:03:46,665 --> 00:03:49,292
If you don't want that jaw of yours
to get dislocated again,

44
00:03:49,376 --> 00:03:51,294
you'd better tell me the truth.

45
00:03:52,212 --> 00:03:54,339
Were you the one who ratted him out?

46
00:03:54,422 --> 00:03:57,425
[scoffs] "Rat him out"?
What do you mean, "rat him out"?

47
00:03:57,509 --> 00:03:59,761
I'll knock your teeth out, damn it.

48
00:03:59,844 --> 00:04:02,305
You want to go?

49
00:04:02,389 --> 00:04:04,266
Being old won't save you.

50
00:04:04,349 --> 00:04:05,934
You little shit…

51
00:04:06,017 --> 00:04:07,602
"You little shit."

52
00:04:07,686 --> 00:04:10,230
I don't go easy on thugs either.

53
00:04:10,981 --> 00:04:12,649
What? "Thug"?

54
00:04:12,732 --> 00:04:15,318
-Say that again!
-Oh, no…

55
00:04:15,402 --> 00:04:18,154
I'm not holding back anymore!

56
00:04:18,655 --> 00:04:22,367
I'm busy, so why don't all three of you
jump me all at once?

57
00:04:22,450 --> 00:04:23,827
Come on.

58
00:04:23,910 --> 00:04:27,873
Bring it!

59
00:04:28,498 --> 00:04:32,085
[groaning]

60
00:04:33,879 --> 00:04:35,297
[sighs]

61
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:37,966
[Yeom groaning]

62
00:04:38,049 --> 00:04:42,637
But you said
you don't know how to do this.

63
00:04:42,721 --> 00:04:44,139
What?

64
00:04:44,222 --> 00:04:47,893
You said you don't know how to do this!

65
00:04:47,976 --> 00:04:49,519
Oh, I don't know how to do this?

66
00:04:49,603 --> 00:04:50,937
-Yes.
-That's right.

67
00:04:52,355 --> 00:04:55,984
Unfortunately, the only doctor who knows
how to reset a jaw is currently suspended.

68
00:04:59,154 --> 00:05:00,739
Wait.

69
00:05:02,407 --> 00:05:05,368
[yelling]

70
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:13,376
Just so you know, I'm pretty bad at this.

71
00:05:15,795 --> 00:05:22,052
-[bones crackling]
-[Yeom groaning]

72
00:05:29,392 --> 00:05:31,102
[Ms. Hwang] Hey, take your meds.

73
00:05:31,186 --> 00:05:32,979
That'll be 1,100 won.

74
00:05:35,982 --> 00:05:39,527
Does the staff here hold a grudge
against me or something?

75
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:43,198
Are you really asking
because you don't know?

76
00:05:43,281 --> 00:05:48,495
It's because you keep going around
spreading weird rumors!

77
00:05:48,578 --> 00:05:49,913
"Weird rumors"?

78
00:05:49,996 --> 00:05:52,624
What do you mean, "weird rumors"?

79
00:05:53,291 --> 00:05:54,501
Damn it!

80
00:05:59,965 --> 00:06:01,174
[door opens]

81
00:06:03,176 --> 00:06:04,344
[door closes]

82
00:06:06,846 --> 00:06:10,392
Where did it…

83
00:06:13,436 --> 00:06:14,771
[Hari] Here.

84
00:06:14,854 --> 00:06:16,231
-[button clicks]
-[both chuckle]

85
00:06:16,314 --> 00:06:17,899
[Ms. Hwang] Here it is.

86
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:27,158
Oh, Dr. Do's not in right now.

87
00:06:31,413 --> 00:06:33,289
Can we talk for a moment?

88
00:06:40,296 --> 00:06:43,299
[Hwayeong] What's going to happen
to Jiui now?

89
00:06:44,259 --> 00:06:47,303
Once he's removed from his post,
he'll be leaving this place,

90
00:06:48,888 --> 00:06:52,016
and he'll be serving the rest of
his military service on active duty.

91
00:06:57,939 --> 00:06:59,858
I heard from Dr. Do

92
00:07:00,567 --> 00:07:02,610
that he lost a friend on an island.

93
00:07:04,487 --> 00:07:07,031
And that he's receiving
the overdue punishment now.
STYLE
::cue()

94
00:07:12,454 --> 00:07:13,663
But you know what?

95
00:07:14,664 --> 00:07:17,167
I don't think he should be punished
for what happened.

96
00:07:17,792 --> 00:07:19,502
He did nothing wrong, after all.

97
00:07:21,337 --> 00:07:24,591
I can't let him hate himself
while he's being punished for it.

98
00:07:30,388 --> 00:07:32,265
Well…

99
00:07:32,348 --> 00:07:33,641
Ms. Yuk.

100
00:07:36,770 --> 00:07:38,521
Please don't hold Jiui back.

101
00:07:39,647 --> 00:07:40,815
What?

102
00:07:41,524 --> 00:07:44,068
Don't break Jiui's heart anymore
with words like that.

103
00:07:45,862 --> 00:07:47,155
[chuckles]

104
00:07:48,323 --> 00:07:52,619
I was the one who told the county office
that Jiui was on medication.

105
00:07:53,286 --> 00:07:54,287
What?

106
00:07:54,996 --> 00:07:56,414
But why on earth would you--

107
00:07:56,498 --> 00:08:00,293
I thought you heard all about why
an island is hell for Jiui.

108
00:08:02,796 --> 00:08:07,967
Jiui and I suffered for a long time.

109
00:08:12,555 --> 00:08:14,682
People say you should
get over your pain, right?

110
00:08:16,267 --> 00:08:17,393
[chuckles]

111
00:08:18,061 --> 00:08:19,062
No.

112
00:08:20,063 --> 00:08:23,441
The only way to treat unbearable pain
is to run away from it.

113
00:08:24,317 --> 00:08:26,194
That's why Jiui wants to leave.

114
00:08:26,277 --> 00:08:27,779
It's because he wants to live.

115
00:08:36,538 --> 00:08:38,164
I'm here to ask you…

116
00:08:40,583 --> 00:08:42,460
not to try and stop Jiui from leaving.

117
00:08:45,213 --> 00:08:46,631
I'm begging you.

118
00:08:51,136 --> 00:08:52,512
Do you really think…

119
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:58,434
leaving the island will help him recover?

120
00:09:08,653 --> 00:09:11,990
He'll get better
once he leaves this place.

121
00:09:35,847 --> 00:09:38,975
TRANSFER DIRECTIVE FOR DERELICTION OF DUTY
BY PUBLIC HEALTH DOCTOR

122
00:09:39,058 --> 00:09:40,518
NAME: DO JIUI

123
00:09:45,398 --> 00:09:46,691
[knocking on door]

124
00:09:47,442 --> 00:09:48,443
[door opens]

125
00:09:50,528 --> 00:09:51,529
Want to have a drink?

126
00:09:58,328 --> 00:10:00,371
Are you really going to leave?

127
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:06,669
I'm sorry for putting you through
so much trouble.

128
00:10:08,671 --> 00:10:12,508
There's no need to apologize.
It just sounds a bit selfish. That's all.

129
00:10:17,388 --> 00:10:22,352
I don't think PH docs should have to
take the fall for something like this.
STYLE
::cue()

130
00:10:38,868 --> 00:10:40,620
PYEONDONG GODDESS

131
00:10:41,788 --> 00:10:43,248
[line ringing]

132
00:10:44,916 --> 00:10:49,462
[voicemail] The number you have dialed
cannot be reached at this moment.

133
00:10:49,545 --> 00:10:50,546
What the heck?

134
00:10:52,507 --> 00:10:54,133
-Ms. Hwang.
-What is it?

135
00:10:54,217 --> 00:10:57,136
Did Ms. Jeongseon go somewhere?
I haven't seen her today.

136
00:10:57,220 --> 00:10:58,221
Lift your leg.

137
00:10:58,304 --> 00:11:01,474
She used her monthly leave,
saying she had to go somewhere urgently.

138
00:11:01,557 --> 00:11:04,686
Huh? Why did she use
a monthly leave all of a sudden?

139
00:11:04,769 --> 00:11:06,104
Why are you asking me that?

140
00:11:06,187 --> 00:11:08,398
You, of all people, should know what's up.

141
00:11:08,481 --> 00:11:10,608
Did you get into
a lovers' quarrel or something?

142
00:11:10,692 --> 00:11:12,610
[stammers] No, it's not like that.

143
00:11:12,694 --> 00:11:16,030
Are you sure you're not
just unaware of it?

144
00:11:16,114 --> 00:11:20,493
She did seem kind of down,
but are you suggesting that was a fight?

145
00:11:21,035 --> 00:11:22,954
You really don't know?

146
00:11:23,037 --> 00:11:26,749
You don't know
whether you got into a fight or not?

147
00:11:28,293 --> 00:11:31,879
Did we really get into a fight?

148
00:11:34,382 --> 00:11:36,551
I swear she was happy, though.

149
00:11:37,635 --> 00:11:40,471
How on earth did you get into
the College of Korean Medicine?

150
00:11:40,555 --> 00:11:42,932
-[line ringing]
-It's the darndest thing.

151
00:11:51,024 --> 00:11:52,275
[phone buzzing]

152
00:11:56,529 --> 00:11:59,699
LOVELY NINNYHAMMER

153
00:12:07,665 --> 00:12:09,459
LOVELY NINNYHAMMER

154
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:20,553
-Thank you.
-[gynecologist] Thank you.

155
00:12:20,636 --> 00:12:22,513
-Take care.
-Okay.

156
00:12:32,732 --> 00:12:33,858
[phone buzzes]

157
00:12:38,571 --> 00:12:40,531
[Jucheon] Where are you, Ms. Eom?

158
00:12:40,615 --> 00:12:42,950
Have I upset you by any chance?

159
00:12:46,913 --> 00:12:50,583
-Ms. Eom Jeongseon.
-Yes.

160
00:12:50,666 --> 00:12:53,086
Please come into the examination room.

161
00:12:53,169 --> 00:12:54,170
Okay.

162
00:12:56,839 --> 00:13:00,468
Your blood test came back as 110,
which means you're definitely pregnant.

163
00:13:02,637 --> 00:13:04,138
I see.

164
00:13:07,016 --> 00:13:09,936
So I really am pregnant.

165
00:13:10,019 --> 00:13:11,396
I really am.

166
00:13:14,065 --> 00:13:17,193
It's still early, so I'm not sure
we'll see a gestational sac,

167
00:13:17,276 --> 00:13:19,570
but would you like to do an ultrasound?

168
00:13:19,654 --> 00:13:21,614
-No.
-Huh?

169
00:13:23,157 --> 00:13:25,034
I don't want to do the ultrasound.

170
00:13:25,118 --> 00:13:27,161
I don't think I need it.

171
00:13:27,954 --> 00:13:29,455
I see.

172
00:13:31,082 --> 00:13:37,797
But my morning sickness has been
causing me some trouble, so…

173
00:13:40,174 --> 00:13:42,051
I'll write you a prescription.

174
00:13:42,135 --> 00:13:43,469
Please wait outside.

175
00:13:43,553 --> 00:13:44,554
Okay.

176
00:14:01,487 --> 00:14:04,490
DAILECTIN

177
00:14:07,285 --> 00:14:09,203
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

178
00:14:31,893 --> 00:14:35,021
[Hwayeong] He'll get better
once he leaves this place.

179
00:14:40,484 --> 00:14:41,652
Ms. Yuk.

180
00:14:44,739 --> 00:14:45,823
Ms. Yuk?

181
00:14:45,907 --> 00:14:47,366
Oh, hey.

182
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:50,494
What's on your mind?
I called you multiple times.

183
00:14:52,205 --> 00:14:54,916
It's nothing.

184
00:14:59,587 --> 00:15:01,047
Are you okay?

185
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:07,720
I don't know.

186
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:45,841
I'm good.

187
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:51,055
I took it off because it's hot.

188
00:15:51,973 --> 00:15:52,974
Right.

189
00:15:53,891 --> 00:15:56,811
But since I took it off,
let me hang it on you for a bit.

190
00:16:02,650 --> 00:16:03,818
[Hari sighs]

191
00:16:05,695 --> 00:16:08,656
Looking out into the sea
always brings me peace of mind.

192
00:16:12,952 --> 00:16:15,913
It's always there for me,
just the way I remember it.

193
00:16:19,583 --> 00:16:23,462
No matter when I return,
or how I've changed,

194
00:16:23,546 --> 00:16:25,381
it's always right here.

195
00:16:30,678 --> 00:16:32,888
Even if everything else leaves me…

196
00:16:35,558 --> 00:16:37,977
the sea will always be here for me.

197
00:16:40,938 --> 00:16:42,398
But I found out…

198
00:16:44,775 --> 00:16:47,778
that this everlasting ocean…

199
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:57,663
was a source of never-ending pain
for someone else.

200
00:17:09,258 --> 00:17:10,593
And that really…

201
00:17:18,768 --> 00:17:20,478
[voice cracking] …breaks my heart.

202
00:17:41,457 --> 00:17:44,543
Dr. Yong, what are you doing here?

203
00:17:44,627 --> 00:17:45,628
Ms. Eom!

204
00:17:45,711 --> 00:17:47,254
Where on earth were you all day?

205
00:17:47,338 --> 00:17:48,923
I couldn't reach you at all.

206
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,258
Did we have a fight?

207
00:17:52,051 --> 00:17:53,469
What are you talking about?

208
00:17:54,095 --> 00:17:55,262
Right?

209
00:17:55,346 --> 00:17:57,056
So we didn't fight, right?

210
00:17:57,139 --> 00:18:00,393
Then why didn't you pick up the phone?

211
00:18:00,476 --> 00:18:02,853
-I was kind of scared for a bit.
-[chuckles]

212
00:18:02,937 --> 00:18:05,272
That's no reason to wait
in front of my house.

213
00:18:05,356 --> 00:18:07,483
It's cold outside.

214
00:18:07,566 --> 00:18:11,612
Well, there was something
I wanted to discuss with you.

215
00:18:13,364 --> 00:18:14,949
Discuss with me?
STYLE
::cue()

216
00:18:19,370 --> 00:18:21,747
[sighs] This is nice.

217
00:18:21,831 --> 00:18:25,835
I'm actually dying to know
where you've been,

218
00:18:25,918 --> 00:18:30,047
but healthy relationships need boundaries,
so I won't ask.

219
00:18:31,048 --> 00:18:33,634
So what did you want to discuss with me?

220
00:18:35,219 --> 00:18:36,429
Uh…

221
00:18:37,096 --> 00:18:38,097
Well…

222
00:18:39,849 --> 00:18:40,850
The thing is…

223
00:18:42,643 --> 00:18:44,937
I have to apply for a transfer soon.

224
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:49,942
Transfer, huh?

225
00:18:52,111 --> 00:18:53,904
I've thought it over,

226
00:18:53,988 --> 00:18:58,075
and I think I should work
somewhere near my dad's hospital next.

227
00:18:59,785 --> 00:19:01,537
What do you think?

228
00:19:03,414 --> 00:19:05,958
I guess you should do that.

229
00:19:06,792 --> 00:19:11,881
To be honest,
I was really conflicted since you're here,

230
00:19:11,964 --> 00:19:15,843
but to start working at my dad's hospital
as soon as I'm done being a PH doc,

231
00:19:15,926 --> 00:19:18,053
I'll need a lot of clinical experience,

232
00:19:18,137 --> 00:19:21,849
but the cases around here are all
pretty much the same, so…

233
00:19:22,975 --> 00:19:26,312
By your dad's hospital,
are you talking about the one in Seoul?

234
00:19:26,395 --> 00:19:28,773
Yes, on Baeng Baeng Intersection.

235
00:19:31,358 --> 00:19:33,444
You're getting farther and farther away.

236
00:19:34,987 --> 00:19:36,197
What?

237
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:37,782
It's nothing.

238
00:19:37,865 --> 00:19:40,534
But why bother discussing that with me?

239
00:19:40,618 --> 00:19:42,411
You should go if you have to go.

240
00:19:42,495 --> 00:19:45,039
Of course, I should ask you.

241
00:19:45,122 --> 00:19:47,833
This is a very important decision for us.

242
00:19:47,917 --> 00:19:50,544
Besides, we like each other,

243
00:19:50,628 --> 00:19:54,048
so we owe it to each other
to discuss important matters beforehand.

244
00:20:04,016 --> 00:20:05,017
[gags]

245
00:20:38,008 --> 00:20:40,052
Oh, my…

246
00:20:43,389 --> 00:20:44,473
Gosh.

247
00:20:44,557 --> 00:20:48,853
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

248
00:20:48,936 --> 00:20:52,356
[Jeongseon] Yikes, you should really watch
where you're going.

249
00:20:52,439 --> 00:20:53,774
-Are you okay?
-[Ms. Hwang] Yeah.

250
00:20:53,858 --> 00:20:55,943
I didn't see a frozen patch on the ground.

251
00:20:56,026 --> 00:20:58,028
You should have been more careful.

252
00:20:58,112 --> 00:21:03,617
Being careful won't help you avoid
the inevitable in life. [chuckles]

253
00:21:03,701 --> 00:21:05,119
Yeah, you're right.

254
00:21:07,913 --> 00:21:09,832
Ms. Eom, something on your mind recently?
STYLE
::cue()

255
00:21:11,876 --> 00:21:13,586
Something on my mind?

256
00:21:13,669 --> 00:21:14,670
Not at all.

257
00:21:14,753 --> 00:21:15,880
Yeah, right.

258
00:21:17,339 --> 00:21:19,633
You've been acting really strange.

259
00:21:19,717 --> 00:21:24,263
You don't complain or pout
as much as you used to.

260
00:21:24,346 --> 00:21:26,891
Something feels really off.

261
00:21:28,392 --> 00:21:30,060
Nothing gets past you.

262
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:32,688
Well, what is it?

263
00:21:34,607 --> 00:21:40,195
It's just, I feel like I'm damned if I do
and damned if I don't,

264
00:21:40,279 --> 00:21:43,324
so I'm just trying to figure out
which way would hurt less.

265
00:21:44,283 --> 00:21:45,409
You're "damned"?

266
00:21:46,243 --> 00:21:47,870
What do you mean you're "damned"?

267
00:21:50,331 --> 00:21:51,749
Huh?

268
00:21:54,793 --> 00:21:55,794
What the…

269
00:21:56,629 --> 00:21:58,255
I guess it's a secret.

270
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:00,925
-[chuckles]
-[scoffs]

271
00:22:09,558 --> 00:22:13,020
When every path seems
to lead you to a cliff

272
00:22:14,146 --> 00:22:17,566
and it feels like the whole world
is out to get you,

273
00:22:18,609 --> 00:22:21,779
you just need to stick close
to the people who are on your side.

274
00:22:23,530 --> 00:22:25,574
It won't hurt as much when you fall.

275
00:22:26,742 --> 00:22:31,455
Having someone who can cry with you
will make it a little better.

276
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:36,502
Is Dr. Jucheon not up to the task?

277
00:22:38,921 --> 00:22:41,382
It's not like that.

278
00:22:43,509 --> 00:22:45,052
Tell me if you ever need me.

279
00:22:45,719 --> 00:22:47,805
You know I cry easily.

280
00:22:49,723 --> 00:22:52,601
Having someone to cry with you
will make it a little better, okay?

281
00:22:52,685 --> 00:22:54,561
We can pass the tissue around and all.

282
00:22:57,898 --> 00:22:58,941
Okay.

283
00:23:04,071 --> 00:23:06,490
[Ms. Hwang] This too shall pass, okay?

284
00:23:06,573 --> 00:23:08,784
This too shall pass.

285
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:10,119
Goodness.

286
00:23:50,451 --> 00:23:52,244
[mouse clicking]

287
00:23:57,541 --> 00:23:58,751
Someone on my side?
STYLE
::cue()

288
00:24:15,309 --> 00:24:17,144
What the…

289
00:24:26,612 --> 00:24:27,946
What was that…

290
00:24:29,406 --> 00:24:31,700
DON'T SKIP YOUR MEALS, DR. DO

291
00:24:33,827 --> 00:24:36,538
FEELING DOWN?
HERE'S A PICK-ME-UP!

292
00:24:43,879 --> 00:24:45,339
[sighs]

293
00:24:46,715 --> 00:24:48,342
[phone buzzes, chimes]

294
00:24:53,639 --> 00:24:56,517
[Hari] Dr. Do,
can you help me with something?

295
00:25:01,105 --> 00:25:02,439
Ta-da!

296
00:25:03,982 --> 00:25:05,275
You're here.

297
00:25:07,736 --> 00:25:08,946
I mean…

298
00:25:10,114 --> 00:25:11,281
What is all this?

299
00:25:11,990 --> 00:25:14,910
Let's make Christmas preparations
for our clinic together.

300
00:25:20,624 --> 00:25:21,667
[exclaims]

301
00:25:24,795 --> 00:25:26,672
Come on, is that the best you can do?

302
00:25:26,755 --> 00:25:28,257
It's too high up.

303
00:25:28,882 --> 00:25:30,551
I got it.

304
00:25:30,634 --> 00:25:32,302
-I got it.
-You got it.

305
00:25:34,179 --> 00:25:37,850
Does the clinic always set up
a Christmas tree like this every year?

306
00:25:37,933 --> 00:25:40,519
I wouldn't know.
This is my first Christmas here too.

307
00:25:42,062 --> 00:25:43,105
Ah.

308
00:25:43,188 --> 00:25:46,066
I just wanted to see you
and needed a good excuse,

309
00:25:46,817 --> 00:25:48,944
so this is what I came up with.

310
00:25:53,448 --> 00:25:55,117
It seemed like a solid excuse

311
00:25:56,493 --> 00:25:58,620
to trick my awkward boyfriend
into coming down.

312
00:26:06,003 --> 00:26:07,004
I'm sorry.

313
00:26:11,383 --> 00:26:12,384
Don't be.

314
00:26:13,302 --> 00:26:14,970
I'm the one who should be apologizing.

315
00:26:20,017 --> 00:26:25,063
I had no idea what you were going through,
but I clung to you anyway.

316
00:26:30,444 --> 00:26:32,738
I was the one who said
you should cross the ocean,

317
00:26:33,530 --> 00:26:35,699
and I'm the one who begged you to return.

318
00:26:38,493 --> 00:26:41,872
You must have struggled so much here,
surrounded on all sides by the ocean.

319
00:26:47,294 --> 00:26:49,004
Surrounded or not,

320
00:26:50,756 --> 00:26:53,425
I wanted to hang in there
because I had you, Ms. Yuk. But…

321
00:26:58,847 --> 00:27:00,140
I'm sorry.

322
00:27:07,356 --> 00:27:09,858
Looks like we just keep having to
apologize to each other.

323
00:27:21,536 --> 00:27:25,040
I had a million lines to say
to get you to stay…

324
00:27:27,084 --> 00:27:29,336
but seeing you now,
I don't think I should.

325
00:27:33,090 --> 00:27:34,341
Can you just…

326
00:27:39,346 --> 00:27:41,932
promise me one thing?

327
00:27:49,648 --> 00:27:52,192
That promise you made to yourself
to never be happy again.

328
00:27:55,529 --> 00:27:56,989
Don't keep it.

329
00:28:01,451 --> 00:28:04,079
I really want to hold on to you so much,

330
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:07,666
but the reason I'm not doing so…

331
00:28:14,673 --> 00:28:17,134
is because I want you to be happy.
STYLE
::cue()

332
00:28:36,486 --> 00:28:37,821
[Hari clears throat]

333
00:28:43,910 --> 00:28:45,078
Come on.

334
00:28:45,162 --> 00:28:47,873
You weren't very good in art class
when you were a kid, right?

335
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,627
Hey, I was even in an art club
back in elementary school.

336
00:28:52,711 --> 00:28:54,546
My teacher said I was really good at art.

337
00:28:55,255 --> 00:28:56,673
Who was your teacher?

338
00:28:57,382 --> 00:29:00,469
They really filled your head
with lies, huh?

339
00:29:07,059 --> 00:29:08,226
Ms. Hwang.

340
00:29:08,310 --> 00:29:09,644
[Ms. Hwang] What's all this?

341
00:29:09,728 --> 00:29:11,813
It's Christmas,
so we wanted to liven things up.

342
00:29:11,897 --> 00:29:14,983
[chuckles] It sure is nice to work with
such young coworkers.

343
00:29:15,067 --> 00:29:17,194
Wow, it looks like
a department store in here.

344
00:29:18,528 --> 00:29:19,988
Gosh, it's so pretty.

345
00:29:21,156 --> 00:29:22,532
So pretty.

346
00:29:23,700 --> 00:29:26,912
I left something here,
so I'm just here to get it.

347
00:29:29,915 --> 00:29:33,251
Oh, that hurts.

348
00:29:45,388 --> 00:29:47,099
Jeez, I don't see it anywhere.

349
00:29:48,475 --> 00:29:50,102
Goodness.

350
00:29:53,605 --> 00:29:56,817
Goodness me.

351
00:29:58,110 --> 00:30:00,237
Where could I have put it?

352
00:30:01,488 --> 00:30:02,572
Is everything all right?

353
00:30:02,656 --> 00:30:03,657
It's nothing.

354
00:30:04,282 --> 00:30:05,617
Now, where could it be?

355
00:30:05,700 --> 00:30:08,703
It's nothing? You can't even see
what's right in front of you.

356
00:30:08,787 --> 00:30:10,956
Hey, I told you it's nothing.

357
00:30:11,039 --> 00:30:15,001
-Take a seat here for a moment.
-I told you I'm okay.

358
00:30:16,628 --> 00:30:17,796
Seriously.

359
00:30:26,972 --> 00:30:29,099
[Jiui] I think you should go
to the hospital right now.

360
00:30:29,182 --> 00:30:31,852
Hey, I'm okay.
There's nothing to worry about.

361
00:30:31,935 --> 00:30:33,353
I'm not a patient or anything.

362
00:30:33,436 --> 00:30:35,355
Or I could introduce you to a doctor--

363
00:30:35,438 --> 00:30:38,692
I told you to leave me alone!
I'll take care of it myself!

364
00:30:41,278 --> 00:30:44,197
Ms. Hwang, why…

365
00:30:47,075 --> 00:30:48,076
Oh…

366
00:30:52,747 --> 00:30:55,250
I just need to wait it out
a little longer.

367
00:30:55,917 --> 00:31:01,923
Something felt off about my eyes
a few months ago, so I got insurance.

368
00:31:02,007 --> 00:31:04,551
But I was told that
I'd have to wait another three months

369
00:31:04,634 --> 00:31:06,928
before they could cover my condition.

370
00:31:12,517 --> 00:31:17,397
It's pretty ironic that a nurse is trying
to ignore her own illness, right?

371
00:31:18,148 --> 00:31:19,733
But what can I do?

372
00:31:19,816 --> 00:31:22,819
Life will go on even after
I'm done treating my sickness.

373
00:31:23,904 --> 00:31:28,992
If we go bankrupt because I'm sick,
how will we pay for our son's education?

374
00:31:29,659 --> 00:31:32,537
[voice cracking]
Our eldest son's a very smart boy

375
00:31:33,371 --> 00:31:37,250
and he said his dream is
to study overseas in the States.

376
00:31:40,712 --> 00:31:41,796
He's got a dream, okay?

377
00:31:44,341 --> 00:31:48,053
What kind of mother would I be
if I got in the way of his dreams?

378
00:31:52,182 --> 00:31:56,102
Things were better when I was young enough
to only worry about whatever ailed me.

379
00:31:56,186 --> 00:31:58,688
Now, the sickness doesn't scare me.

380
00:31:58,772 --> 00:32:00,398
The bills do.

381
00:32:08,281 --> 00:32:11,701
Life can be really unfair.

382
00:32:12,994 --> 00:32:14,371
So unfair.

383
00:32:19,209 --> 00:32:21,962
I wasn't done making dinner,
so I should hurry back.

384
00:32:24,839 --> 00:32:27,008
Thank you.

385
00:32:29,803 --> 00:32:31,221
[clears throat]

386
00:32:35,642 --> 00:32:37,227
[door opens]

387
00:32:41,147 --> 00:32:42,816
-[sighs]
-[door closes]
STYLE
::cue()

388
00:32:52,284 --> 00:32:54,577
I came across people like her
a lot in the ER.

389
00:32:55,829 --> 00:32:58,164
People who hide their condition,

390
00:32:58,999 --> 00:33:01,584
not because they're scared of it,
but because of the costs.

391
00:33:05,297 --> 00:33:10,635
Whether it's then or now,
there's still nothing I can do for her.

392
00:33:22,731 --> 00:33:24,190
[phone buzzing]

393
00:33:24,274 --> 00:33:25,859
Just a sec.

394
00:33:32,032 --> 00:33:33,825
-Hello?
-[Jinbae] Hey, Hari.

395
00:33:33,908 --> 00:33:36,119
You need to come right now.

396
00:33:37,037 --> 00:33:41,166
LUCKY SUPERMARKET

397
00:33:41,249 --> 00:33:42,250
What is it, Granny?

398
00:33:42,334 --> 00:33:44,252
-This man came into the supermarket…
-[man groaning]

399
00:33:44,336 --> 00:33:47,380
…looking for painkillers
and then just collapsed.

400
00:33:47,464 --> 00:33:49,341
He's sweating bullets

401
00:33:49,424 --> 00:33:52,135
and shaking like a leaf.

402
00:33:52,218 --> 00:33:57,140
I told him we should go to the center,
but he was vehemently against that.

403
00:33:57,223 --> 00:33:58,224
Goodness.

404
00:34:04,272 --> 00:34:05,690
Are you okay, sir?

405
00:34:10,737 --> 00:34:12,614
I'll try pressing you
like I did back then.

406
00:34:12,697 --> 00:34:15,575
[groaning]

407
00:34:18,036 --> 00:34:20,580
[groans intensely]

408
00:34:21,456 --> 00:34:22,540
Dr. Do.

409
00:34:25,585 --> 00:34:28,213
-It's the same symptoms as before.
-Should I call a chopper?

410
00:34:29,381 --> 00:34:31,883
The painkillers made the pain go away,

411
00:34:31,966 --> 00:34:35,595
and the folks at the hospital
said the scans came out clean.

412
00:34:37,263 --> 00:34:41,893
I already feel terrible
for causing the death of that pilot

413
00:34:41,976 --> 00:34:45,605
and damaging your reputation.

414
00:34:48,608 --> 00:34:50,151
I'm just going to go now.

415
00:34:50,235 --> 00:34:51,528
[groans]

416
00:34:51,611 --> 00:34:53,822
-Sir.
-Dr. Do.

417
00:34:53,905 --> 00:34:55,365
We should get him to a hospital.

418
00:34:55,448 --> 00:34:56,658
Okay.

419
00:34:57,909 --> 00:34:59,452
Hang in there, sir.

420
00:35:00,370 --> 00:35:02,622
No, you can't…

421
00:35:05,709 --> 00:35:09,003
[line rings]

422
00:35:09,087 --> 00:35:11,464
-Yeopoong-gun operations center.
-This is Pyeondongdo.

423
00:35:11,548 --> 00:35:14,259
We have a suspected appendicitis
needing immediate transfer.

424
00:35:14,342 --> 00:35:16,428
[official] Isn't that
where that accident happened?

425
00:35:16,511 --> 00:35:18,847
We can't dispatch anyone
under current emergency protocols.

426
00:35:18,930 --> 00:35:21,808
What's that got to do with this?
There's a patient here.

427
00:35:21,891 --> 00:35:23,768
Well, the sea fog is too thick,

428
00:35:23,852 --> 00:35:25,812
and we don't have any choppers on standby.

429
00:35:25,895 --> 00:35:27,439
A man is dying right now!

430
00:35:27,522 --> 00:35:30,400
I'm sorry, but due to protocol,
we can't offer you any assistance.

431
00:35:30,483 --> 00:35:31,484
-I'm sorry.
-Hey--

432
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:33,570
Hello?

433
00:35:38,533 --> 00:35:40,952
[Jinbae] Hey, do you have a minute?

434
00:35:41,619 --> 00:35:44,539
We could use your help here.

435
00:35:45,874 --> 00:35:47,876
Careful. Take it slow…

436
00:35:49,753 --> 00:35:51,463
Won't it be dangerous, Mr. Park?

437
00:35:51,546 --> 00:35:53,965
We can't let a man die
because it's a little dangerous,

438
00:35:54,048 --> 00:35:55,383
not after I lived like that!

439
00:35:55,467 --> 00:35:58,178
If you say he needs to go,
we're getting him there!

440
00:35:59,304 --> 00:36:00,513
I'm sorry.

441
00:36:00,597 --> 00:36:02,432
Hey, don't say that.

442
00:36:02,515 --> 00:36:05,018
Why would you feel sorry
for wanting to live?

443
00:36:05,101 --> 00:36:06,686
You just hang in there, okay?

444
00:36:08,563 --> 00:36:09,731
[Hwayeong] Jiui.

445
00:36:11,232 --> 00:36:12,567
Think it over.

446
00:36:12,650 --> 00:36:14,277
You're on probation.
If something goes wrong,

447
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:17,155
you might actually have to
step down as a doctor for good.

448
00:36:17,238 --> 00:36:18,865
Let's wait it out a little longer.

449
00:36:21,868 --> 00:36:24,037
What if he were to lose his life?
STYLE
::cue()

450
00:36:25,455 --> 00:36:28,458
We'd be powerless to do anything,
just like back then.

451
00:36:36,466 --> 00:36:38,760
-Let's go, Mr. Park.
-Okay.

452
00:36:38,843 --> 00:36:41,596
Hold on tight, folks.
The winter winds are brutal!

453
00:36:44,224 --> 00:36:45,558
Let me help you put one on.

454
00:37:03,076 --> 00:37:04,911
Please take good care of him.

455
00:37:04,994 --> 00:37:06,496
Save him! That's all we ask!

456
00:37:06,579 --> 00:37:12,877
Oh, mighty Dragon King,
please grant our people safe passage.

457
00:37:12,961 --> 00:37:13,962
Goodness…

458
00:37:14,045 --> 00:37:16,047
[♪ dramatic music playing]

459
00:37:26,599 --> 00:37:28,601
[sirens wailing]

460
00:37:30,144 --> 00:37:32,522
This is a patient
previously transferred for R/O appy.

461
00:37:32,605 --> 00:37:34,899
He now has
localized RLQ tenderness and rebound.

462
00:37:34,983 --> 00:37:36,693
He's running a temp of 37.7

463
00:37:36,776 --> 00:37:38,611
-and experiencing chills.
-Got it.

464
00:37:44,784 --> 00:37:46,494
EMERGENCY DISPATCH

465
00:37:46,578 --> 00:37:50,832
[sirens wailing]

466
00:37:57,130 --> 00:37:58,298
[sighs]

467
00:38:05,054 --> 00:38:06,306
[breathes shakily]

468
00:38:07,974 --> 00:38:10,310
[chuckles] Dr. Do, here.

469
00:38:10,977 --> 00:38:12,395
Have a sip while it's hot.

470
00:38:12,478 --> 00:38:15,231
-Thank you.
-[chuckles, sighs]

471
00:38:17,984 --> 00:38:20,862
Damn, that really
hits the spot. [inhales sharply]

472
00:38:20,945 --> 00:38:22,405
[sighs]

473
00:38:25,116 --> 00:38:26,159
[smacks lips, inhales deeply]

474
00:38:26,784 --> 00:38:28,912
[sighs] By the way, Dr. Do…

475
00:38:30,204 --> 00:38:31,706
Are you really leaving?

476
00:38:34,751 --> 00:38:37,712
Come on.
Why not fight for yourself a bit longer?

477
00:38:39,923 --> 00:38:41,758
Would that be too much to ask of you?

478
00:38:45,720 --> 00:38:46,971
I'm sorry.

479
00:38:47,513 --> 00:38:48,765
[Mr. Park sighs]

480
00:38:48,848 --> 00:38:51,392
What's causing you so much pain?

481
00:38:52,185 --> 00:38:58,566
When I heard you were on medication,
hearing that really broke my heart.

482
00:39:00,944 --> 00:39:05,406
You risked your life many times to save us
while taking medication yourself,

483
00:39:05,490 --> 00:39:08,701
so sending you off like this
without protecting you…

484
00:39:09,953 --> 00:39:12,497
[sighs] It just doesn't feel right.

485
00:39:16,125 --> 00:39:20,630
At times like this,
living on an island feels like a crime.

486
00:39:21,381 --> 00:39:22,799
[chuckles] It truly does…

487
00:39:23,549 --> 00:39:24,968
[both sigh]

488
00:39:25,051 --> 00:39:26,511
[footsteps approaching]

489
00:39:26,594 --> 00:39:27,762
[Hari] Dr. Do!

490
00:39:30,682 --> 00:39:33,601
They just started operating
on the patient for appendicitis.

491
00:39:33,685 --> 00:39:37,271
It went unnoticed last time
because the appendix was obscured,

492
00:39:37,355 --> 00:39:39,232
but he's just gone into emergency surgery.

493
00:39:40,149 --> 00:39:41,567
[sighs]

494
00:39:41,651 --> 00:39:44,320
They said it was a really close call.

495
00:39:45,738 --> 00:39:49,242
You saved this patient's life, Dr. Do.

496
00:39:49,325 --> 00:39:53,329
[chuckles] Wow. So he made it, huh?

497
00:39:53,413 --> 00:39:55,331
He made it. [chuckles]

498
00:39:58,835 --> 00:40:00,336
Goodness.
STYLE
::cue()

499
00:40:13,808 --> 00:40:15,226
What's on your mind?

500
00:40:19,689 --> 00:40:21,774
That appendicitis patient.

501
00:40:23,359 --> 00:40:25,528
He apologized to me.

502
00:40:27,739 --> 00:40:31,951
Despite the pain and fear of death.

503
00:40:33,911 --> 00:40:36,873
[Hari] Treatments that would be considered
trivial on the mainland

504
00:40:36,956 --> 00:40:39,417
aren't very accessible on an island.

505
00:40:40,877 --> 00:40:43,671
That's why people end up
losing their lives… [sighs]

506
00:40:43,755 --> 00:40:47,300
…over some stupid lights or appendicitis.

507
00:40:50,261 --> 00:40:55,058
To save someone's life,
one must put their own life on the line.

508
00:40:58,394 --> 00:41:00,980
I guess that's why
islanders here apologize

509
00:41:01,064 --> 00:41:04,275
before begging the doctor
to save their lives.

510
00:41:07,070 --> 00:41:09,947
Because they're afraid
someone might get hurt because of them.

511
00:41:13,534 --> 00:41:15,244
But that's unacceptable.

512
00:41:17,371 --> 00:41:18,581
Hmm.

513
00:41:18,664 --> 00:41:20,333
I mean, wanting to live shouldn't be…

514
00:41:22,001 --> 00:41:24,087
something you have to apologize for.

515
00:41:32,095 --> 00:41:37,892
-[Mr. Park] All right, let's go!
-[Hari] Okay. Let's get up.

516
00:41:42,063 --> 00:41:44,023
-[Hari chuckles]
-[inhales sharply]

517
00:41:44,107 --> 00:41:45,566
You two go on without me.

518
00:41:46,567 --> 00:41:48,152
-What?
-[Mr. Park] Huh?

519
00:41:48,236 --> 00:41:49,278
Dr. Do!

520
00:41:50,988 --> 00:41:52,740
Huh?

521
00:42:00,206 --> 00:42:01,374
2025-2026 YEOPOONG-GUN

522
00:42:01,457 --> 00:42:03,292
EMERGENCY MEDICAL CARE
MODERNIZATION PLAN

523
00:42:04,418 --> 00:42:07,421
Handle things quietly from now on

524
00:42:07,505 --> 00:42:11,050
if you want to keep your job
as director, got it?

525
00:42:12,885 --> 00:42:13,886
Yes, sir.

526
00:42:16,097 --> 00:42:18,057
[Mr. Choi] You can't just
barge in here like this.

527
00:42:18,141 --> 00:42:19,142
I said you can't!

528
00:42:19,225 --> 00:42:20,518
[Changmok] What the hell?

529
00:42:20,601 --> 00:42:22,895
[panting]

530
00:42:22,979 --> 00:42:25,857
It'll be in your best interest
to talk to me right now.

531
00:42:25,940 --> 00:42:27,942
Otherwise, I might just take these files

532
00:42:28,025 --> 00:42:30,528
straight to those reporters
that you like so much.

533
00:42:32,822 --> 00:42:34,198
Leave us.

534
00:42:40,454 --> 00:42:42,206
[door closes]

535
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:48,212
I can't accept your decision
to remove me from my PH doc post.

536
00:42:48,296 --> 00:42:50,298
[laughs]

537
00:42:50,381 --> 00:42:54,385
Well, I guess you're here
to throw a tantrum like a baby, huh?

538
00:42:56,721 --> 00:42:59,599
INSPECTION OF FAULTY HELIPAD
CONSTRUCTION IN YEOPOONG-GUN

539
00:42:59,682 --> 00:43:03,311
[Jiui] I have evidence that proves
that out of the 20 helipads

540
00:43:03,394 --> 00:43:05,771
renovated in Yeopoong-gun,
17 had faulty lighting.

541
00:43:05,855 --> 00:43:08,691
Even on the night of the accident
at the Pyeondongdo helipad,

542
00:43:08,774 --> 00:43:11,277
the lights weren't working properly.

543
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:13,529
[Changmok sighs]

544
00:43:13,613 --> 00:43:19,452
So it wasn't a misdiagnosis,
but the helipad was the problem?

545
00:43:19,535 --> 00:43:22,496
I mean, why should we believe
the words of a PH doc

546
00:43:22,580 --> 00:43:25,082
who's taking psychiatric medicine?

547
00:43:25,166 --> 00:43:28,169
Regardless of that fact
and the possibility of misdiagnosis,

548
00:43:28,794 --> 00:43:31,088
the helicopter should've landed safely.

549
00:43:33,966 --> 00:43:37,303
A proper system is what saves lives
in medically underserved regions,

550
00:43:37,386 --> 00:43:40,223
not a skilled doctor.

551
00:43:41,557 --> 00:43:44,852
A system that gets patients
the care they need as soon as possible.

552
00:43:48,981 --> 00:43:53,986
What killed that pilot
was Yeopoong-gun's shitty system.

553
00:43:56,322 --> 00:43:59,325
The hell did you say? "Shitty system"?

554
00:43:59,408 --> 00:44:02,536
Apologize to the family
of the crash victim right this instant.

555
00:44:04,497 --> 00:44:07,041
The only reason I'm giving you
a chance to fix this

556
00:44:08,084 --> 00:44:09,752
is because I also believe

557
00:44:11,504 --> 00:44:13,839
that system could save lives.

558
00:44:13,923 --> 00:44:19,720
YEOPOONG-GUN
HEALTHCARE MODERNIZATION

559
00:44:25,685 --> 00:44:27,061
Dr. Do Jiui!

560
00:44:31,649 --> 00:44:32,692
[sighs]

561
00:44:32,775 --> 00:44:37,113
Do you really think
you can bring about change?

562
00:44:39,991 --> 00:44:43,995
The more you provoke the governor,
the worse things will get for you.
STYLE
::cue()

563
00:44:47,415 --> 00:44:49,709
PH docs are civil servants

564
00:44:50,584 --> 00:44:54,547
which gives the governor the power
to discipline and penalize them at will.

565
00:44:55,339 --> 00:44:57,341
[♪ sentimental music plays]

566
00:44:58,634 --> 00:44:59,844
PH docs…

567
00:45:01,512 --> 00:45:02,847
[sighs]

568
00:45:03,556 --> 00:45:04,890
…are also doctors.

569
00:45:08,394 --> 00:45:09,895
Even when the odds are against us…

570
00:45:12,732 --> 00:45:14,525
we have a duty to save lives.

571
00:45:38,007 --> 00:45:39,216
[Geumja] Here.

572
00:45:39,300 --> 00:45:41,093
[Mar. Park sighs]

573
00:45:41,177 --> 00:45:44,680
-[Mr. Park] That looks amazing.
-[Jinbae] And it's perfectly seasoned.

574
00:45:45,890 --> 00:45:50,186
[Mr. Park] So you're saying you don't have
to leave anymore, Dr. Do?

575
00:45:50,269 --> 00:45:52,772
That you'll be here for the full year?

576
00:45:52,855 --> 00:45:55,483
[Jangsu] Geez, stop asking him that.

577
00:45:55,566 --> 00:45:57,902
He said it hasn't been settled yet.

578
00:45:57,985 --> 00:46:00,154
No, I'll make it so.

579
00:46:00,237 --> 00:46:01,489
[Jangsu] Oh, right.

580
00:46:01,572 --> 00:46:04,825
That's great news,
considering all you've been through!

581
00:46:04,909 --> 00:46:06,827
I know, right?

582
00:46:06,911 --> 00:46:09,997
We were worried sick that he might
get dragged off to active duty.

583
00:46:10,081 --> 00:46:11,665
[all chuckle]

584
00:46:11,749 --> 00:46:12,792
Thank you.

585
00:46:14,960 --> 00:46:17,755
About that medication I'm on--

586
00:46:17,838 --> 00:46:20,674
No. You don't owe us an explanation.

587
00:46:20,758 --> 00:46:23,677
Everyone's on some kind of medication.

588
00:46:23,761 --> 00:46:25,721
I take twenty pills
a day just to keep going!

589
00:46:25,805 --> 00:46:26,806
[Jangsu] Exactly.

590
00:46:26,889 --> 00:46:29,100
If taking medicine is a crime,

591
00:46:29,183 --> 00:46:31,852
then everyone in this room
is serving a life sentence.

592
00:46:31,936 --> 00:46:35,439
[Sugwang] That's true,
a life sentence. [chuckles]

593
00:46:37,400 --> 00:46:38,984
[Geumja] Goodness, hurry and eat now.

594
00:46:41,028 --> 00:46:42,029
[gags]

595
00:46:42,113 --> 00:46:45,825
[Jangsu] He's more of a softie
than you might think.

596
00:46:49,203 --> 00:46:54,041
Keep crying like that,
and you're gonna make me cry too.

597
00:46:56,502 --> 00:46:59,213
DAILECTIN - FOR NAUSEA
AND VOMITING OF PREGNANCY

598
00:47:01,340 --> 00:47:03,843
[indistinct chattering, laughing]

599
00:47:15,312 --> 00:47:16,355
Oh, my…

600
00:47:21,986 --> 00:47:23,779
How are your eyes?

601
00:47:23,863 --> 00:47:27,116
[chuckles] Well, you know… [clears throat]

602
00:47:28,534 --> 00:47:29,535
[sighs]

603
00:47:30,870 --> 00:47:33,414
I wanted to ask you something.

604
00:47:33,497 --> 00:47:35,249
Yes?

605
00:47:36,375 --> 00:47:39,587
How did you muster
that kind of courage? Hmm?

606
00:47:40,337 --> 00:47:43,257
If it hadn't turned out
to be appendicitis,

607
00:47:43,340 --> 00:47:45,968
you really would have lost your license.

608
00:47:48,012 --> 00:47:49,972
Um… [sighs]

609
00:47:50,556 --> 00:47:53,476
Well, we had to save him first…

610
00:47:55,394 --> 00:47:57,730
before we could worry
about what happens next.

611
00:47:57,813 --> 00:48:00,065
[♪ sincere music playing]

612
00:48:01,901 --> 00:48:05,654
Besides, I had known it all along.

613
00:48:07,656 --> 00:48:08,741
Known what?

614
00:48:10,618 --> 00:48:13,037
I knew the people here
wouldn't turn their backs on me,

615
00:48:13,120 --> 00:48:15,539
no matter what happened.

616
00:48:19,752 --> 00:48:22,296
Of course not! [chuckles]

617
00:48:23,130 --> 00:48:24,215
Of course not.

618
00:48:25,049 --> 00:48:26,509
[Mr. Park] Dr. Do!

619
00:48:26,592 --> 00:48:29,386
What are you doing? Come here for a drink!

620
00:48:29,470 --> 00:48:31,013
[chuckles] Yes, I'm coming.

621
00:48:31,096 --> 00:48:34,475
Where are you?

622
00:48:34,558 --> 00:48:36,393
What are you doing here? Get back in here.

623
00:48:36,477 --> 00:48:39,063
-I said I'm coming.
-Don't make him drink too much.

624
00:48:39,146 --> 00:48:42,566
-Hey, come here.
-Sit.

625
00:48:42,650 --> 00:48:45,486
-[Geumja] Go easy on him!
-[Jangsu] You're all dead meat today!

626
00:48:45,569 --> 00:48:46,737
[Sugwang] Yeah, right.

627
00:48:46,820 --> 00:48:48,280
-Bring us more booze!
-All right.

628
00:48:48,364 --> 00:48:51,116
[Mr. Park] It's a drink-off then, okay?

629
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:53,911
[indistinct chattering, laughing]

630
00:49:01,001 --> 00:49:02,878
[line ringing]

631
00:49:07,049 --> 00:49:08,759
Hey, honey.

632
00:49:09,885 --> 00:49:15,057
I need you to come
to the hospital with me on Monday.

633
00:49:19,353 --> 00:49:22,273
I think I'm a little sick. [chuckles]

634
00:49:23,482 --> 00:49:24,525
[exclaims]

635
00:49:27,695 --> 00:49:28,862
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

636
00:49:39,582 --> 00:49:41,125
Are you leaving now?

637
00:49:44,670 --> 00:49:45,671
Yeah.

638
00:49:52,553 --> 00:49:56,181
I never thought we'd stand before
the ocean together like this again.

639
00:49:59,393 --> 00:50:01,812
I thought it would never happen again.

640
00:50:10,487 --> 00:50:11,572
[inhales deeply]

641
00:50:14,033 --> 00:50:15,409
Jiui.

642
00:50:19,163 --> 00:50:21,498
When I walked out on you back then…

643
00:50:23,542 --> 00:50:25,711
I didn't do it
because I blamed you for it.

644
00:50:28,922 --> 00:50:30,424
I felt like if we stayed together…

645
00:50:30,507 --> 00:50:32,134
[inhales deeply]

646
00:50:32,217 --> 00:50:34,386
…we'd just end up resenting each other.

647
00:50:37,222 --> 00:50:38,641
But…

648
00:50:42,645 --> 00:50:45,189
since I've been here,
I couldn't help but think…

649
00:50:47,107 --> 00:50:50,569
"Would things have been more bearable
if we had stayed together?"

650
00:50:58,786 --> 00:51:00,788
You weren't the only one
who walked out on me.

651
00:51:03,332 --> 00:51:05,292
I did the same thing.

652
00:51:07,878 --> 00:51:13,300
I ran away from everything
that reminded me of Seonu…

653
00:51:16,220 --> 00:51:18,764
constantly blaming myself
for failing to save him.

654
00:51:21,809 --> 00:51:22,893
But…

655
00:51:26,105 --> 00:51:28,982
don't you think things might have
turned out a little differently…

656
00:51:30,818 --> 00:51:32,528
if someone had helped us out back then?

657
00:51:35,823 --> 00:51:36,824
If only we had…

658
00:51:39,618 --> 00:51:42,287
gotten to the hospital a little sooner.

659
00:51:45,040 --> 00:51:46,417
If only…

660
00:51:49,002 --> 00:51:51,380
Seonu had gotten proper treatment sooner.

661
00:51:54,675 --> 00:51:56,135
Don't you think things might have…

662
00:51:58,387 --> 00:52:00,597
turned out a little differently
for Seonu and us?

663
00:52:10,858 --> 00:52:11,942
Hwayeong.

664
00:52:20,284 --> 00:52:21,744
Why don't we…

665
00:52:24,705 --> 00:52:27,124
forgive ourselves now?

666
00:52:32,171 --> 00:52:34,006
We tried our best back then.

667
00:52:41,680 --> 00:52:43,015
[inhales sharply]

668
00:52:43,098 --> 00:52:44,391
[breathes shakily]

669
00:52:45,726 --> 00:52:46,810
[chuckles]

670
00:52:49,021 --> 00:52:50,481
[cries, sniffles]

671
00:52:54,318 --> 00:52:55,444
What about you?

672
00:52:58,739 --> 00:53:01,033
Have you forgiven yourself?
STYLE
::cue()

673
00:53:16,507 --> 00:53:17,925
[breathes shakily]

674
00:53:18,008 --> 00:53:20,260
We should find happiness now.

675
00:53:46,370 --> 00:53:47,579
I'm sorry.

676
00:53:49,790 --> 00:53:52,751
[inhales sharply, cries]

677
00:53:57,130 --> 00:53:58,340
[sniffles]

678
00:54:23,448 --> 00:54:25,117
What brings you here?

679
00:54:27,494 --> 00:54:29,079
Do you have anything to tell me?

680
00:54:31,707 --> 00:54:33,125
What are you talking about?

681
00:54:34,459 --> 00:54:36,378
I'm asking if you have
something to tell me.

682
00:54:37,713 --> 00:54:40,007
Stop talking in riddles.

683
00:54:46,763 --> 00:54:48,807
You're pregnant.

684
00:54:48,890 --> 00:54:51,893
[♪ soft music playing]

685
00:54:51,977 --> 00:54:55,564
Was the reason
you haven't been feeling well recently

686
00:54:55,647 --> 00:54:57,149
because you're pregnant?

687
00:54:59,568 --> 00:55:01,528
When you suddenly took a day off,

688
00:55:01,612 --> 00:55:04,990
did you go to the hospital alone
without telling me?

689
00:55:08,243 --> 00:55:09,244
I did.

690
00:55:12,831 --> 00:55:16,043
And you had no intention
of ever telling me, right?

691
00:55:17,210 --> 00:55:18,211
Right?

692
00:55:20,464 --> 00:55:23,842
Say something!

693
00:55:23,925 --> 00:55:25,844
Why did you do that?

694
00:55:28,889 --> 00:55:32,392
It's because
I haven't made a decision yet.

695
00:55:35,729 --> 00:55:38,398
You're only here temporarily, Dr. Yong.

696
00:55:38,482 --> 00:55:42,819
You may feel like you're really into me,
but your world is back in Seoul,

697
00:55:42,903 --> 00:55:45,447
at a high-end clinic
on Baeng Baeng Intersection

698
00:55:45,530 --> 00:55:47,824
where you'd be a big-shot doctor
of Korean medicine.

699
00:55:47,908 --> 00:55:51,703
And my world is this tiny, dusty village.

700
00:55:51,787 --> 00:55:55,582
I don't think people like us can coexist
in the same space for too long.

701
00:55:59,294 --> 00:56:01,797
Is that why you weren't
ever going to tell me?

702
00:56:05,384 --> 00:56:07,177
Do you really have so little faith in me?

703
00:56:07,260 --> 00:56:09,388
This isn't about you.

704
00:56:10,931 --> 00:56:13,058
I don't have any faith in myself.

705
00:56:15,602 --> 00:56:17,020
Ms. Eom.

706
00:56:18,438 --> 00:56:21,483
This is just the way I am…

707
00:56:24,569 --> 00:56:26,780
so don't waste your time
worrying about me.

708
00:56:29,783 --> 00:56:31,535
I'm going to do things my way.

709
00:56:47,426 --> 00:56:51,680
-[ship horn blows]
-[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

710
00:56:57,394 --> 00:56:59,312
Here, try some.

711
00:57:00,188 --> 00:57:01,356
-Is it good?
-Yeah!

712
00:57:13,201 --> 00:57:15,036
It's good, isn't it?

713
00:57:15,120 --> 00:57:16,455
[chuckles]

714
00:57:19,332 --> 00:57:20,792
[exclaims]

715
00:57:20,876 --> 00:57:22,294
I love this. [chuckles]

716
00:57:23,420 --> 00:57:24,963
What do you mean?

717
00:57:25,046 --> 00:57:27,716
Having you here. [chuckles]

718
00:57:32,304 --> 00:57:33,805
[clears throat]

719
00:57:34,389 --> 00:57:35,432
So…

720
00:57:37,225 --> 00:57:42,814
I'm going to go see Seonu tomorrow.

721
00:57:44,399 --> 00:57:46,193
Because I haven't said goodbye yet.

722
00:57:47,027 --> 00:57:48,278
Oh…

723
00:57:48,987 --> 00:57:52,407
Can you come with me?

724
00:57:56,286 --> 00:58:00,624
I feel like I'll be able to go
if you come with me.

725
00:58:06,129 --> 00:58:09,007
[♪ sincere music playing]

726
00:59:05,605 --> 00:59:09,860
KIM SEONU

727
00:59:09,943 --> 00:59:12,195
IN MEMORY OF OUR FRIEND,
KIM SEONU,

728
00:59:12,279 --> 00:59:14,114
WHO WOULD HAVE MADE
AN AMAZING DOCTOR

729
00:59:14,197 --> 00:59:18,326
HANGUK UNIVERSITY
MEDICAL SCHOOL CLASS OF 2014

730
00:59:37,178 --> 00:59:38,221
Seonu.

731
00:59:46,855 --> 00:59:48,523
[cries] Seonu, I'm sorry.

732
00:59:50,609 --> 00:59:51,943
[cries]

733
00:59:55,739 --> 00:59:57,657
I'm sorry I kept you waiting so long.

734
00:59:58,742 --> 01:00:01,411
[crying]

735
01:00:39,157 --> 01:00:42,327
[crying continues]

736
01:00:49,000 --> 01:00:50,502
[Jiui sighs]

737
01:00:54,422 --> 01:00:56,091
Thank you…

738
01:00:59,970 --> 01:01:01,805
for coming to see Seonu with me today.

739
01:01:03,974 --> 01:01:08,269
Thank you for staying with me.

740
01:01:09,062 --> 01:01:11,064
[both chuckle]

741
01:01:12,607 --> 01:01:15,986
[Jiui] I think
this is where I first met you.

742
01:01:17,570 --> 01:01:20,031
What was that like?
Did you think I was cute?

743
01:01:20,824 --> 01:01:21,866
[inhales sharply]

744
01:01:21,950 --> 01:01:23,368
Hmm…

745
01:01:23,451 --> 01:01:24,577
You were a little scary.

746
01:01:25,453 --> 01:01:27,622
What the heck?

747
01:01:27,706 --> 01:01:28,707
Seriously?

748
01:01:29,624 --> 01:01:35,046
They say there are three things a PH doc
must avoid on an island, you see.

749
01:01:35,630 --> 01:01:37,966
Three things? What are they?

750
01:01:38,883 --> 01:01:41,011
They say if you don't avoid
those three things,

751
01:01:41,094 --> 01:01:43,054
you'll never leave an island.

752
01:01:45,974 --> 01:01:47,308
Incidents…
STYLE
::cue()

753
01:01:51,104 --> 01:01:54,566
people, and…

754
01:01:56,526 --> 01:01:57,569
love.

755
01:02:02,365 --> 01:02:04,242
[both chuckle]

756
01:02:08,204 --> 01:02:09,914
I think I knew back then…

757
01:02:11,916 --> 01:02:14,252
that I was never going to leave.

758
01:02:14,335 --> 01:02:18,381
[♪ romantic pop music playing]

759
01:02:59,881 --> 01:03:01,716
[♪ music fades]

760
01:03:04,427 --> 01:03:05,428
[tires screech]

761
01:03:06,137 --> 01:03:07,639
ON OFFICIAL DUTY

762
01:03:24,114 --> 01:03:27,367
[♪ dramatic music playing]

763
01:03:27,450 --> 01:03:30,829
YEOPOONG-GUN

764
01:03:35,125 --> 01:03:37,460
We're with the Yeopoong-gun
Audit Department.

765
01:03:37,544 --> 01:03:40,755
Stop what you're doing
and cooperate with our investigation.

766
01:03:42,215 --> 01:03:45,176
Dr. Jiui! This is bad!

767
01:03:45,260 --> 01:03:49,222
You need to come down
to the center right now!

768
01:03:53,810 --> 01:03:54,936
DO NOT APPROACH

769
01:03:55,019 --> 01:03:59,023
Those are patient records.
You're not supposed to touch those.

770
01:03:59,107 --> 01:04:01,401
Excuse me!

771
01:04:01,484 --> 01:04:02,861
Keep going.

772
01:04:02,944 --> 01:04:04,571
What do you think you're doing?

773
01:04:05,697 --> 01:04:08,783
We have reason to believe this center
is involved in a kickback scheme.

774
01:04:08,867 --> 01:04:10,827
Kickbacks? What are you talking about?

775
01:04:11,452 --> 01:04:14,497
A recent internal audit uncovered evidence
that this clinic accepted

776
01:04:14,581 --> 01:04:17,876
kickbacks from Manu Pharmaceuticals
in exchange for procuring its drugs.

777
01:04:17,959 --> 01:04:19,919
An investigation is currently underway.

778
01:04:20,003 --> 01:04:22,672
As a result, operations
at the Pyeondong Health Center

779
01:04:22,755 --> 01:04:25,175
will be suspended until
the investigation is concluded.

780
01:04:25,258 --> 01:04:26,718
You're suspending our operations?

781
01:04:28,344 --> 01:04:29,846
[phone buzzing]

782
01:04:36,477 --> 01:04:37,979
Hello?

783
01:04:38,062 --> 01:04:39,814
Hey, Dr. Do Jiui.

784
01:04:39,898 --> 01:04:44,402
I wonder if you received my response yet.

785
01:04:44,485 --> 01:04:50,867
I hope you enjoy a little taste
of that shitty system you mentioned.

786
01:04:51,618 --> 01:04:54,621
The system that teaches
a lowly civil servant

787
01:04:54,704 --> 01:04:57,165
not to mess with the governor, got it?

788
01:04:57,248 --> 01:05:03,296
The kind of system that shows a guard dog
what happens when it barks at its master!

789
01:05:04,589 --> 01:05:06,174
Better get in line.

790
01:05:08,635 --> 01:05:10,553
Punk-ass bastard.

791
01:05:18,519 --> 01:05:20,855
Ko Changmok, that son of a bitch.

792
01:05:25,151 --> 01:05:27,153
[♪ soft music playing]

793
01:05:35,787 --> 01:05:38,539
THAT PROMISE YOU MADE
TO YOURSELF

794
01:05:38,623 --> 01:05:42,252
TO NEVER BE HAPPY AGAIN…

795
01:05:42,335 --> 01:05:46,172
DON'T KEEP IT.

796
01:05:54,430 --> 01:05:57,642
THE BEST KIND OF RAMYEON
IS THE KIND I'M SHARING WITH YOU

797
01:05:58,226 --> 01:06:01,646
SOMEONE ON MY SIDE?

798
01:06:06,651 --> 01:06:09,654
HARI AND I ARE THE SAME AGE

799
01:06:13,741 --> 01:06:16,661
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

800
01:06:17,287 --> 01:06:18,830
[Jucheon] We'll be transferring soon.

801
01:06:18,913 --> 01:06:21,207
[Ms. Hwang] It's about time
you returned to your place.

802
01:06:21,291 --> 01:06:23,584
[Hari] I have something to tell you,
Dr. Do.

803
01:06:23,668 --> 01:06:24,919
[car crashes]

804
01:06:25,003 --> 01:06:26,170
Hey!

805
01:06:26,254 --> 01:06:28,923
[Ms. Hwang] If any of you touch
a single thing here, it's theft.

806
01:06:29,007 --> 01:06:31,301
I don't think the center
should be shut down,

807
01:06:31,384 --> 01:06:33,678
which is why I've come up with a solution.

808
01:06:33,761 --> 01:06:36,055
[Hyeon] I'd say this is a no-brainer.

809
01:06:36,139 --> 01:06:38,558
[Hari] I'm the one who stole this, so…

810
01:06:38,641 --> 01:06:40,852
[Jucheon] Something terrible will happen
if you keep this up!

811
01:06:40,935 --> 01:06:43,146
[Jiui] I'm going to keep
fighting until the end.

812
01:06:47,025 --> 01:06:49,027
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park

